# menu_enter_launch.numos — Phase 9B Main Menu ENTER-launch parity (golden-free).
#
# Companion to menu_nav_parity.numos. That script proves arrow focus moves match
# the firmware 2D grid; THIS one proves the other half of the contract: after
# grid navigation, pressing ENTER still launches the card that is currently
# FOCUSED (not whatever LVGL's linear order would have selected). It is the
# end-to-end check that navigation + activation compose correctly.
#
# Why it matters: the Phase 9B dispatch change routes launcher arrows through
# MainMenu::moveFocusByDelta (which calls lv_group_focus_obj), while ENTER keeps
# going through the existing LVGL keypad path (NativeHal.cpp dispatchKey MENU
# branch). If those two ever desynced, ENTER would click the wrong card. Here we
# RIGHT once (focus Calculation id0 -> Grapher id1), confirm the focus, then
# ENTER and assert Grapher actually opened.
#
# Grapher is launchApp id 1 in the emulator — the same id as the launcher's
# Grapher card — so a correct focus+ENTER lands in GrapherApp.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/menu_enter_launch.numos \
#           --frames 600 --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 4 assertion failure.

log "menu_enter_launch: waiting for splash -> launcher"
wait 200

# Start on Calculation (id 0), step RIGHT to focus Grapher (id 1).
assert_menu_focus Calculation
key right
assert_menu_focus Grapher

# ENTER activates the FOCUSED card via LVGL CLICKED -> onCardEvent -> launchApp(1).
key enter
wait 120

# If focus and activation are in sync, the active app is now Grapher.
assert_app Grapher
log "menu_enter_launch: PASS - ENTER launched the focused Grapher card"
